{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778468777261,"sessionID":"ses_1eb07b402ffeX2iVbnr0m2LegA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:42","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git add src/ontology/go-edit.obo && git commit -m 'Add new term: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine (GO:7770074)\n\nAdds a new biological process term for protein O-linked glycosylation\nvia N-acetylglucosamine (O-GlcNAcylation) as a child of GO:0006493.\n\nThis term represents the covalent linkage of a single N-acetylglucosamine\nvia a beta-glycosidic bond to serine/threonine residues, in contrast to\nother O-linked glycosylations where the sugar is typically elongated.\n\nCloses #32044'","description":"Commit new GO term"},"output":"[scribe-v1-ai4curation-go-ontology-agent-config-v9-.-togetherai-moonshotai-Kimi-K2.6-iter1-issue-32044 ec475b3] Add new term: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine (GO:7770074)\n 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)\n","metadata":{"output":"[scribe-v1-ai4curation-go-ontology-agent-config-v9-.-togetherai-moonshotai-Kimi-K2.6-iter1-issue-32044 ec475b3] Add new term: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine (GO:7770074)\n 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)\n","exit":0,"description":"Commit new GO term","truncated":false},"title":"Commit new GO term","time":{"start":1778468777257,"end":1778468777260}},"id":"prt_e14ffdf61001ogfDrOG3JLRy4h","sessionID":"ses_1eb07b402ffeX2iVbnr0m2LegA","messageID":"msg_e14ffd047001AjmNnTgsw7gcSp"}}
